snippet.textDisplay: If Ruiz could not take the rematch seriously & train hard, when it was the biggest fight in boxing! From the build-up to the fight, it was as big as it gets, then why would it be any different in a 3rd fight?? For me, I would want to see Ruiz win, against top opposition, whilst in great shape, before getting excited about a trilogy! Ruiz keeps pushing for a third fight in all his interviews, he does not seem to realise that, the second fight was his big chance & he has blow it! Joshua now has 2 mandatories to deal with, so even if AJ wanted the 3rd Ruiz fight, it couldn't happen!! But it seems that Ruiz, will be given another chance at world title, as the WBC have announced that Andy is eligible for a fight with Wilder! Which I find unbelievable given that Wilder & Fury have a possible 2 more fights planned, back to back, then Dillian Whyte should be next inline, there shouldn't even be the possibility of Ruiz getting a Wilder shot until Whyte finally get his fight!! (Will be interesting to read what everyone thinks in the comments)
